member.remarks:
Window procedures return an LRESULT value to indicate the outcome of message processing. The meaning of this value depends on the message sent to the window.
On 64-bit Windows, LRESULT is defined as a 64-bit signed integer (LONG_PTR). On 32-bit Windows, it is a 32-bit signed integer (LONG).
This type is declared in WinDef.h as follows: typedef LONG_PTR LRESULT;
